Under a &quot;symmetrizability&quot; assumption, formula_2 identifies with the derived subalgebra formula_19 of the affine Kac-Moody algebra formula_20 defined below.

== Definition ==
Assume we are given an formula_21 generalized Cartan matrix of rank &quot;r&quot;. For every such formula_22, there exists a unique up to isomorphism &quot;realization&quot; of formula_22, i.e. a triple formula_24) where formula_25 is a complex vector space, formula_26 is a subset of elements of formula_25, and formula_28 is a subset of the dual space formula_29 satisfying the following three conditions:

# The vector space formula_25 has dimension 2&quot;n&quot; − &quot;r&quot; 
# The sets formula_28 and formula_26 are linearly independent and 
# For every formula_33. 

The formula_34 are analogue to the simple roots of a semi-simple Lie algebra, and the formula_35 to the simple coroots.

Then we define the &quot;Kac-Moody algebra&quot; associated to formula_22 as the Lie algebra formula_37 defined by generators formula_3 and formula_5 and the elements of formula_25 and relations 
*formula_41 for formula_42;
