*If formula_12 (so formula_13) then formula_14 and formula_15, where formula_16 is the adjoint representation of formula_17.

A real (possibly infinite-dimensional) Lie algebra is also considered a Kac–Moody algebra if its complexification is a Kac–Moody algebra.

==Root-space decomposition of a Kac–Moody algebra==
formula_25 is the analogue of a Cartan subalgebra for the Kac–Moody algebra formula_17.

If formula_57 is an element of formula_17 such that

